# Force LF line endings on checkout regardless of platform (Phase 61,
# ADR-0079). Without this, Windows' default `core.autocrlf=true` converts
# committed LF to CRLF on checkout, which silently changes the exact byte
# content of every text file -- and therefore every hash `detect-secrets`
# computes over it, causing the Windows CI leg to see "new" secrets that
# are really just the same content with different line endings. Real bug,
# found by CI actually running on windows-latest (ADR-0056's own
# "explicit-UTF-8 cross-platform contract... actually running on it, not
# skipped" precedent) rather than assumed to work.
* text=auto eol=lf
